This paper deals with privacy in data publishing, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on anonymization techniques, which are commonly used in databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) to protect sensitive information. The paper also discusses the use of side information, which is relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
